%2Famp_articleshow%2F105202212.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Finternal-documents-show-the-world-health-organization-paid-sexual-abuse-victims-in-congo-250-each%2Famp_articleshow%2F105202212.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20cop%20mowed%20down%20by%20tractor%20carrying%20illegally%20mined%20sand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699943424000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105202042%2Cimgsize-25406.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fpatna%2Fbihar-cop-killed-by-mining-mafia-tractor-police-sub-inspector-mowed-down-by-tractor-carrying-illegally-mined-sand-in-bihars-jamui%2Farticleshow%2F105202051.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fpatna%2Fbihar-cop-killed-by-mining-mafia-tractor-police-sub-inspector-mowed-down-by-tractor-carrying-illegally-mined-sand-in-bihars-jamui%2Farticleshow%2F105202051.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Afghanistan's%20Rashid%20Khan%3A%20Children%20Of%20Conflict%2C%20Now%20Cricket%20Stars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20Rashid%20Khan's%20age%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20asked%20my%20dad%2C%20who%20is%20a%20serious%20cricket%20fan.%20%26quot%3B32%20or%20so...%26quot%3B%20was%20his%20answer.%20%26quot%3BWrong%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20and%20my%20%3Cem%3Enani%20%3C%2Fem%3E(maternal%20grandmother)%20were%20born%20in%20Bannu%2C%20a%20town%20in%20North%20Waziristan%2C%20close%20to%20Pakistan's%20border%20with%20Afghanistan.%20So%2C%20with%2075%20per%20cent%20of%20my%20genes%20from%20the%20North-West%20frontier%2C%20I%20am%20a%20natural%20fan%20of%20the%20Afghanistan%20cricket%20team.%20Also%2C%20I%20stay%20in%20Greater%20Noida%2C%20which%20has%20been%20their%20'home-away-from-home'%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20to%20Rashid%20Khan.%20Most%20people%20are%20surprised%20to%20hear%20that%20Afghan%20cricket's%20rock%20star%20is%20just%2025.%20He%20was%20just%2017%20when%20he%20made%20his%20national%20ODI%20and%20T20%20debut.%20At%2019%2C%20he%20became%20ODI%20captain%2C%20the%20youngest%20to%20captain%20an%20international%20team%20in%20cricket%20history.%20At%2019%2C%20he%20was%20the%20fastest%20to%20100%20ODI%20wickets%20in%20cricket%20history%2C%20at%2021%20the%20fastest%20to%20100%20T20%20wickets%20in%20cricket%20history.%20At%2022%2C%20he%20was%20declared%20ICC's%20T20%20Player%20of%20the%20Decade%2C%20which%20is%20amazing%20as%20he%20was%20just%2012%20when%20the%20decade%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfghanistan%20Catches%20Them%20Young%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfghanistan%20routinely%20bloods%20its%20cricketers%20young.%20Their%20latest%20spin%20sensation%20Noor%20Ahmad%2C%20born%20in%202005%2C%20played%20in%20Australia's%20Big%20Bash%20League%20at%2015.%20By%2017%2C%20he%20was%20playing%20ODI%20and%20T20%20cricket%20for%20his%20country%2C%20and%20is%20now%20part%20of%20Afghanistan's%20'spin%20quartet'%20of%20Rashid%2C%20Nabi%2C%20Mujib%20and%20himself.%20He%20is%20not%20alone.%20His%20fellow%20spinner%2C%20Mujeeb%20ur%20Rahman%2C%20is%20just%2022%2C%20and%20went%20for%204%20crores%20in%20the%20IPL%20auction%20when%20he%20was%20just%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfghanistan's%20stellar%20opening%20pair%20in%20this%20World%20Cup%2C%20Rahmanullah%20Gurbaz%20and%20Ibrahim%20Zadran%2C%20are%20both%20just%2021.%20Zadran%20scored%20Afghanistan's%20first%20ODI%20century%20in%20World%20Cup%20history%2C%20that%20too%20against%20mighty%20Australia.%20Hasmatullah%20Shahidi%2C%20the%20Captain%2C%20is%2029%20today%2C%20but%20even%20he%20made%20his%20debut%20at%2019%2C%20and%20is%20the%20first%20Afghan%20to%20score%20a%20double%20hundred%20in%20test%20cricket.%20Azmatullah%20Omarzai%2C%20who%20completes%20their%20hot%20'batting%20quartet'%2C%20is%20just%2023.%20So%20yes%2C%20watch%20out%20for%20this%20team%20all%20over%20again%20at%20the%202027%20World%20Cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERefugee%20Camps%2C%20the%20Cradle%20of%20Afghan%20Cricket%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Afghanistan%2C%20life%20is%20tough.%20You%20have%20to%20grow%20up%20quick%20and%20learn%20your%20skills%20the%20hard%20way.%20Ask%20their%20veteran%20all-rounder%20Mohammad%20Nabi.%20Ask%20their%20current%20assistant%20coach%20and%20former%20player%2C%20Raees%20Ahmedzai.%20Even%20ask%20Rashid%20Khan.%20All%20of%20them%2C%20at%20different%20times%2C%20spent%20years%20of%20their%20childhood%20in%20cramped%20refugee%20camps%20in%20Pakistan.%20Ahmedzai%20was%20born%20at%20a%20camp%20in%20Peshawar%2C%20after%20his%20family%20fled%20during%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Afghanistan%20in%20the%201980s.%20Nabi's%20family%20had%20done%20the%20same.%20Rashid's%20family%20was%20forced%20into%20Pakistan%20after%20the%209%2F11%20bombings%20when%20US%20and%20NATO%20forces%20invaded%20Afghanistan%20to%20take%20on%20the%20Taliban%20and%20Al%20Qaeda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20only%20one%20silver%20lining%20-%20cricket%20-%20which%20these%20future%20stars%20learnt%20to%20play%20at%20the%20refugee%20camps.%20With%20severe%20restrictions%20on%20movement%2C%20their%20families%20strapped%20for%20resources%2C%20these%20children%20of%20conflict%20had%20little%20else%20to%20do%20other%20than%20focus%20on%20cricket.%20Without%20proper%20gear%2C%20often%20with%20no%20footwear%2C%20playing%20on%20concrete%2C%20learning%20from%20games%20on%20TV%2C%20they%20miraculously%20acquired%20world-class%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%20years%20of%20conflict%20-%20even%20as%20Kabul%20lurched%20from%20Taliban%20control%2C%20to%20US%20and%20NATO%20powers%2C%20to%20the%20hands%20of%20a%20tribal%20coalition%2C%20to%20being%20a%20rag-tag%20democracy%2C%20and%20then%20back%20to%20Taliban%20rule%20-%20cricket%20sprang%20roots%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20somehow%20survived.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20did%20more%20than%20survive.%20Thriving%20on%20the%20raw%20talent%20and%20passion%20of%20the%20game's%20pioneers%2C%20the%20country%20made%20a%20mark%20at%20every%20level%2C%20making%20it%20hard%20for%20the%20ICC%20to%20look%20away.%20The%20country%20gained%20ODI%20status%20in%202009%2C%20qualified%20for%20the%20U-19%20World%20Cup%20in%202012%2C%20and%20got%20full%20ICC%20test-cricket%20playing%20member%20status%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20six%20years%20later%2C%20they%20beat%20three%20former%20World%20Cup%20winning%20teams%20-%20England%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%20-%20convincingly.%20They%20even%20had%20mighty%20Australia%20tottering%20at%2091%20for%207%20until%20Glen%20Maxwell%20played%20the%20innings%20of%20his%20life%2C%20to%20deny%20Afghanistan%20a%20possible%20semi-final%20berth.%20No%20team%20went%20past%20300%20against%20them%2C%20and%20their%20confident%2C%20classy%20batting%20has%20won%20many%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERashid%20Khan%20and%20Taliban%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20more%20challenges%20before%20a%20Rashid%20Khan.%20The%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%20is%20the%20Taliban.%20Critics%20want%20a%20massive%20cricket%20star%20like%20Rashid%20Khan%2C%20with%20close%20to%209%20million%20followers%20on%20Instagram%2C%20whom%20the%20world%20media%20and%20cricket%20media%20follow%20closely%2C%20to%20speak%20out%20against%20the%20highly%20conservative%20Taliban%20regime.%20Even%20more%20so%20against%20its%20treatment%20of%20women%2C%20whose%20rights%20to%20education%20and%20employment%2C%20and%20freedom%20of%20movement%20and%20clothing%2C%20are%20now%20severely%20curtailed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20would%20argue%20that%20this%20ask%20from%20Rashid%20Khan%20is%20not%20realistic.%20Militarily%2C%20the%20West%20has%20conceded%20that%20it%20could%20not%20tackle%20the%20Taliban.%20Politically%2C%20while%20the%20world%20makes%20the%20'right%20noises'%2C%20there%20is%20almost%20nothing%20that%20Afghanistan's%20foes%20or%20friends%20seem%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20by%20way%20of%20influencing%2C%20changing%2C%20or%20even%20softening%20the%20Taliban's%20regressive%20ideology.%20Civil%20society%20is%20unable%20to%20take%20on%20the%20Taliban%2C%20as%20the%20judiciary%2C%20the%20law%2C%20the%20police%2C%20media%2C%20every%20institutional%20pillar%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20Taliban.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShould%20Rashid%20Khan%20put%20his%20career%2C%20or%20even%20the%20future%20of%20Afghanistan%20cricket%20at%20risk%20by%20speaking%20out%20against%20the%20Taliban%2C%20who%20also%20control%20cricket%20in%20the%20country%3F%20Just%20as%20the%20Taliban%2C%20almost%20on%20a%20whim%2C%20recognized%20cricket%20in%202000%2C%20they%20could%20as%20easily%20ban%20the%20game%20again.%20Also%2C%20does%20Rashid%20Khan's%20star%20status%20make%20him%20immune%20to%20being%20targeted%2C%20even%20arrest%3F%20Not%20really.%20If%20he%20chose%20to%20be%20a%20critic%20from%20outside%20the%20country%2C%20which%20would%20certainly%20end%20his%20career%2C%20the%20Taliban%20could%20still%20target%20his%20family%20members%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfghan%20Cricketers%20are%20Not%20Politically%20Numb%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERashid%20and%20Nabi%20also%20got%20on%20Twitter%20in%202021%2C%20as%20Taliban%20rule%20returned.%20Not%20naming%20the%20Taliban%20directly%2C%20they%20put%20out%20tweets%20calling%20on%20the%20world%20community%20to%20save%20Afghanistan%20from%20'chaos'.%20But%2C%20since%20then%2C%20it%20has%20clearly%20not%20been%20possible%20for%20them%20to%20speak%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20Afghanistan's%20cricketers%20are%20not%20politically%20numb.%20Right%20through%20the%202023%20World%20Cup%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20news%20of%20Pakistan%20sending%20'undocumented'%20Afghan%20refugees%20back%20to%20Afghanistan.%20It's%20not%20a%20small%20number%20-%20an%20estimated%201.7%20million.%20Sadly%2C%20most%20of%20them%20are%20'undocumented'%20for%20no%20fault%20of%20theirs%2C%20and%20many%20face%20the%20prospect%20of%20being%20prosecuted%20by%20the%20Taliban%20on%20their%20return%2C%20or%20having%20no%20livelihood%20prospects.%20Afghanistan's%20cricketers%20have%20repeatedly%20dedicated%20their%20wins%2C%20and%20their%20Man%20of%20the%20Match%20awards%20to%20the%20plight%20of%20their%20refugee%20fellow%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20for%20a%20Rashid%20Khan%2C%20and%20let%20us%20remember%20he%20is%20just%2025%2C%20activism%20will%20mean%20walking%20a%20very%20thin%2C%20almost%20invisible%2C%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfghanistan%20Women's%20Cricket%20-%20Worth%20Batting%20For%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20possible%20starting%20point%20for%20him%20could%20be%20the%20cause%20of%20women's%20cricket%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20which%20is%20all%20but%20dead.%20A%20women's%20team%20was%20created%20in%202010%2C%20only%20to%20be%20disbanded%20in%202014%20due%20to%20conservative%20pressure%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Taliban%20was%20not%20even%20in%20power.%20In%202020%2C%20there%20was%20progress%20again%2C%20as%2025%20women%20players%20were%20awarded%20contracts%20by%20the%20Afghan%20Cricket%20Board%20(ACB)%2C%20and%20camps%20were%20held%20to%20select%20a%20national%20team.%20But%20after%2015%20August%202021%2C%20when%20the%20Taliban%20rolled%20into%20Kabul%2C%20all%20sports%20for%20women%20was%20banned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Afghan%20women%20cricketers%20have%20since%20left%20the%20country%2C%20and%20most%20of%20them%20have%20re-grouped%20in%20Australia.%20One%20of%20their%20aims%20is%20to%20get%20recognition%20and%20funding%20from%20ACB%2C%20and%20get%20Afghan%20women's%20cricket%20kick-started%20again.%20Rashid%20Khan%20could%20reach%20out%20to%20ACB%20for%20a%20discussion%2C%20or%20start%20mentioning%20the%20aspirations%20of%20the%20women's%20team%20on%20social%20media%2C%20or%20in%20the%20many%20media%20interviews%20he%20does%2C%20could%20use%20his%20star%20power%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20Taliban%20and%20spin%20a%20miracle.%20Cricket%20fans%2C%20after%20seeing%20the%20Afghan%20men%20in%20action%2C%20can%20only%20imagine%20what%20talent%20is%20waiting%20to%20be%20unlocked%20in%20Afghanistan's%20women's%20cricket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI'd%20like%20to%20believe%20that%20even%20the%20most%20regressive%20regimes%20need%20to%20stay%20popular%20by%20backing%20a%20popular%20sport%2C%20and%20even%20the%20most%20regressive%20rulers%20do%20enjoy%20rubbing%20shoulders%20with%20rock%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Rohit%20Khanna%20is%20a%20journalist%2C%20commentator%20and%20video%20storyteller.%20He%20has%20been%20Managing%20Editor%20at%20The%20Quint%2C%20Executive%20Producer%20of%20Investigations%20%26amp%3B%20Special%20Projects%20at%20CNN-IBN%2C%20and%20is%20a%202-time%20Ramnath%20Goenka%20award%20winner)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699943100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fv5sklam_rashid-khan-afghanistan_625x300_14_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fafghanistans-rashid-khan-children-of-conflict-now-cricket-stars-4572455%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWhat's%20Rashid%20Khan's%20age%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20asked%20my%20Dad%2C%20who%20is%20a%20serious%20cricket%20fan.%20%26quot%3B32%20or%20so...%26quot%3B%20was%20his%20answer.%20%26quot%3BWrong%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fafghanistans-rashid-khan-children-of-conflict-now-cricket-stars-4572455%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fafghanistans-rashid-khan-children-of-conflict-now-cricket-stars-4572455%2Famp%2F1