ewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14102103%2FUntitled-design.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20weeks%20of%20declining%20popularity%20and%20effectiveness%2C%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20has%20made%20risky%20changes%20to%20his%20cabinet%20that%20will%20create%20major%20political%20problems%20for%20him%20through%20to%20the%20general%20election%20expected%20late%20next%20year.%20The%20moves%2C%20which%20include%20the%20astonishing%20return%20of%20former%20prime%20minister%20David%20Cameron%20to%20the%20cabinet%2C%20may%20however%20strengthen%20the%20stability%20and%20authority%20of%20his%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%20and%20the%20stability%20both%20come%20from%20Sunak%20sacking%20Suella%20Braverman%2C%20the%20eruptive%2C%20headline-grabbing%20and%20arguably%20irresponsible%20Home%20Secretary%2C%20whose%20frequent%20controversial%20remarks%20climaxed%20with%20statements%20that%20exacerbated%20tensions%20at%20massive%20pro-Palestine%20demonstrations%20over%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman%20was%20sacked%2C%20a%20Downing%20Street%20spokesman%20has%20suggested%2C%20because%20of%20her%20tone%20more%20than%20her%20policies%20and%20because%20she%20ignored%20collective%20cabinet%20responsibility.%20She%20was%20not%20it%20seems%20offered%20a%20new%20post%20and%20will%20now%20try%20to%20seal%20her%20role%20as%20a%20populist%20focal%20point%20for%20the%20turbulent%20right%20wing%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20might%20well%20become%20an%20active%20leadership%20challenger%20for%20Sunak%2C%20but%20he%20would%20have%20looked%20weak%20to%20the%20point%20of%20incompetence%20if%20he%20had%20not%20dared%20to%20sack%20her.%20He%20now%20faces%20potential%20unrest%20in%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20around%20the%20country%20where%20many%20ordinary%20members%20back%20her%20right%20wing%20views%20on%20blocking%20immigration%20and%20tougher%20police%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14102508%2FF9cQMl5XwAA7u-Q.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14102508%2FF9cQMl5XwAA7u-Q.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14102508%2FF9cQMl5XwAA7u-Q-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14102508%2FF9cQMl5XwAA7u-Q-1024x683.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684606%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20X%2F%40SuellaBraverman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20successor%2C%20James%20Cleverly%2C%20has%20risen%20in%20prominence%20as%20foreign%20secretary%20in%20the%20past%20year.%20He%20has%20brought%20respect%20and%20rationality%20to%20the%20role%20after%20three%20predecessors%20generally%20regarded%20as%20failures%20%E2%80%93%20Liz%20Truss%20(later%20briefly%20prime%20minister)%2C%20Dominic%20Raab%20(now%20out%20of%20politics)%20and%20Boris%20Johnson%20(whose%20reputation%20as%20prime%20minister%20lies%20in%20tatters).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20left%20a%20vacancy%20as%20foreign%20secretary%20which%20Sunak%20could%20have%20filled%20uncontroversially%20with%20an%20existing%20member%20of%20the%20cabinet.%20Instead%2C%20he%20has%20brought%20the%20former%20somewhat%20discredited%20prime%20minister%20David%20Cameron%20into%20the%20government%2C%20astonishing%20all%20political%20observers%20and%20indeed%20probably%20all%20MPs%20of%20all%20parties.%20Cameron%20is%20not%20an%20MP%20so%20has%20been%20made%20a%20member%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Lords.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20appointmnt%20drove%20Braverman%E2%80%99s%20sacking%20off%20the%20day%E2%80%99s%20media%20top%20headlines%2C%20but%20it%20will%20be%20widely%20ridiculed%20by%20the%20Labour%20Opposition%20and%20others.%20Cameron%20led%20Britain%20to%20its%20current%20Brexit%20existence%20outside%20the%20European%20Union%20by%20calling%20a%20referendum%20in%202016%20that%20he%20assumed%20would%20be%20in%20favour%20of%20remaining%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20resigned%20in%202016%20(having%20been%20prime%20minister%20since%202010)%20on%20the%20day%20the%20Brexit%20referendum%20result%20was%20announced%20and%20has%20been%20in%20the%20political%20wilderness%20since%20then%2C%20looking%20lost%20without%20any%20role.%20He%20was%20urged%20by%20Boris%20Johnson%20to%20try%20to%20become%20secretary%20general%20of%20NATO%20in%202017%2C%20but%20failed%20to%20secure%20the%20job%20and%20it%20seemed%20his%20public%20life%20was%20finished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%20his%20reputation%20has%20been%20harmed%20by%20lobbying%20he%20carried%20out%20for%20Greensill%20Capital%2C%20a%20scandal-hit%20financial%20services%20company%20that%20collapsed%20in%202021.%20His%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20lack%20of%20judgment%E2%80%9D%20was%20criticised%20by%20a%20Treasury%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20Sunak%20has%20given%20him%20the%20job%2C%20rather%20than%20more%20obvious%20cabinet%20candidates%2C%20is%20presumably%20that%20Cameron%20is%20widely%20experienced%20politically%20and%20is%20well%20known%20internationally.%20He%20will%20gain%20respect%20for%20UK%20policies%20in%20foreign%20capitals%20and%20multi-national%20organisations%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20relevant%20in%20the%20current%20Middle%20East%20crisis%2C%20even%20though%20he%20was%20involved%20as%20prime%20minister%20in%20controversial%20decisions%20including%20support%20for%20a%20NATO-led%20military%20intervention%20in%20Libya%20in%202011%20that%20toppled%20Muammar%20Gadhafi%20but%20led%20to%20chaos.%20In%202013%2C%20he%20tried%20and%20failed%20to%20gain%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20backing%20for%20UK%20airstrikes%20against%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%E2%80%99s%20forces%20in%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForeign%20relations%20are%20an%20area%20where%20Sunak%20has%20little%20experience%20and%2C%20indeed%2C%20has%20at%20times%20seemed%20not%20to%20want%20to%20be%20involved.%20He%20did%20not%20go%20the%20UN%20general%20assembly%20earlier%20this%20year%20and%20tried%20to%20avoid%20the%20climate%20change%20Cop%2027%20summit%20last%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitically%2C%20Cameron%20is%20in%20the%20centre%20of%20Conservative%20Party%20politics%20and%20his%20appointment%20will%20be%20welcomed%20in%20what%20are%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20shires%20and%20%E2%80%9Cblue%20wall%E2%80%9D%20areas%20where%20Tory%20voters%20might%20switch%20to%20other%20parties%20at%20the%20next%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%2C%20the%20appointment%20is%20good%20news%20because%20Cameron%20tried%2C%20albeit%20with%20little%20success%2C%20to%20strengthen%20two-way%20trade%20and%20investment%20when%20he%20was%20prime%20minister.%20He%20made%20three%20visits%20to%20India%20in%20that%20role%20and%20hosted%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20London%20in%202015.%20His%20last%20publicised%20visit%20was%20as%20a%20private%20individual%20in%20December%202016%2C%20when%C2%A0he%20was%20paid%20a%20rumoured%20%C2%A3200%2C000%C2%A0to%20speak%20at%20a%20Hindustan%20Times%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20far%20Cameron%20tries%20to%20move%20British%20policy%20towards%20China%2C%20where%20a%20balance%20needs%20to%20be%20struck%20between%20limited%20co-operation%20on%20key%20issues%20and%20protecting%20security%20concerns%20on%20inward%20investment.%20As%20prime%20minister%2C%20he%20talked%20about%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20age%E2%80%9D%20in%20UK-China%20relations%20and%20welcomed%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20investment%20in%20key%20UK%20nuclear%20power%20and%20iother%20infrastructure%20projects.%20He%20tried%20after%20stepping%20down%20to%20set%20up%20a%20%241bn%20UK-China%20investment%20fund%2C%20but%20that%20was%20abandoned%20two%20years%20ago%20because%20of%20deteriorating%20relations%20with%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECameron%20will%20support%20cautious%20moves%20that%20Sunak%20has%20been%20making%20recently%20to%20grow%20closer%20to%20Europe%2C%20backed%20by%20Jeremy%20Hunt%2C%20who%20remains%20Chancellor%20of%20the%20Exchequer%20(finance%20minister).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman%20leapt%20to%20national%20prominence%20in%20July%202022%20when%20she%20announced%20on%20a%20late%20night%20political%20tv%20programme%20her%20candidacy%20to%20success%20Boris%20Johnson%20(who%20had%20not%20by%20then%20resigned%20as%20prime%20minister).%20She%20immediately%20broke%20convention%20by%20refusing%20to%20resign%20as%20attorney%20general%2C%20an%20early%20indication%20of%20her%20scant%20respect%20for%20parliamentary%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman%20making%20her%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20hurricane%20is%20coming%E2%80%9D%20speech%20at%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20conference%2C%20October%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20candidacy%20was%20not%20treated%20seriously%2C%20and%20she%20was%20quickly%20eliminated%20from%20the%20contest%2C%20but%20the%20move%20launched%20her%20rapid%20elevation%20with%20her%20extreme%20anti-immigration%20and%20pro%20law%20and%20order%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Braverman%20attracted%20widespread%20criticism%20when%20she%20said%20floods%20of%20people%20who%20come%20to%20the%20UK%20across%20the%20Channel%20in%20small%20boats%20%E2%80%9Cpossess%20values%20which%20are%20at%20odds%20with%20our%20country%E2%80%9D%20and%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Cheightened%20levels%20of%20criminality%E2%80%9D.%20She%20told%20The%20Guardian%20her%20claims%20were%20based%20on%20briefings%20from%20unnamed%20senior%20police%20officers%2C%20not%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20claim%20that%20Albanian%20people%20arriving%20in%20the%20UK%20by%20small%20boats%20were%C2%A0exploiting%20modern%20slavery%C2%A0laws%20was%20challenged%20in%20an%20analysis%20seen%20by%20the%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20became%20home%20minister%20under%20prime%20minister%20Liz%20Truss%20last%20year%2C%20but%20resigned%20just%20before%20Truss%20fell%20from%20office%20after%20being%20accused%20of%20breaching%20confidential%20guidelines.%20Sunak%20surprised%20commentators%20by%20reappointing%20her%20to%20the%20same%20job%20when%20he%20became%20prime%20minister%20%E2%80%93%20presumably%20because%20it%20was%20safer%20to%20have%20her%20in%20the%20cabinet%20than%20outside%20because%20of%20her%20outspoken%20right-wing%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20her%20time%20as%20Home%20Secretary%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20debate%20about%20whether%20her%20controversial%20speeches%20are%20made%20from%20conviction%20or%20are%20simply%20part%20of%20her%20campaign%20to%20become%20the%20next%20prime%20minister%20by%20winning%20support%20from%20grassroots%20Conservative%20members%20who%20align%20themselves%20with%20what%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20has%20a%20complex%20ethnic%20identity%20as%20the%C2%A0daughter%20of%20a%20Hindu%20Tamil%20mother%20from%20Mauritius%20and%20a%20Goan%20Christian%20father%C2%A0born%20in%20Kenya%20%E2%80%93%20they%20emigrated%20to%20the%20UK%20in%20the%201960s.%20She%20is%20a%20Buddhist%2C%20belonging%20to%20the%20sometimes%C2%A0controversial%20Triratna%20sect%2C%20and%C2%A0her%20husband%20is%20Jewish.%C2%A0They%20live%20in%20what%20a%20family%20friend%20has%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20very%20Jewish%20part%20of%20the%20country%20in%20Hertfordshire%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%3A%20%E2%80%9CShe%20does%20have%20a%20strong%20relationship%20with%20the%20Jewish%20community.%20People%20have%20been%20very%20quick%20to%20say%20she%20is%20Machiavellian%2C%20but%20she%20sees%20this%20as%20a%20values%20issue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%20very%20wide%20multi-cultural%20background%2C%C2%A0Braverman%20delivered%20an%20incendiary%20speech%20at%20the%20Conservative%20party%20conference%20in%20October%20saying%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cmulti-culturalism%20has%20failed%C2%A0because%20it%20allowed%20people%20to%20come%20to%20our%20society%20and%20live%20parallel%20lives%20in%20it%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98The%20hurricane%20that%20is%20coming%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20made%20a%20speech%20that%20had%20chilling%20echoes%20of%20a%20famous%20%E2%80%9Crivers%20of%20blood%E2%80%9D%20warning%20made%20in%201968%20by%20Enoch%20Powell%2C%20a%20leading%20Conservative%20politician%20about%20how%20Britain%20would%20be%20swamped%20by%20immigrants%20%E2%80%9CThe%20wind%20of%20change%20that%20carried%20my%20own%20parents%20across%20the%20globe%20in%20the%2020th%20century%20was%20a%20mere%20gust%20compared%C2%A0%5Bwith%5D%20the%20hurricane%20that%20is%20coming%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20today%2C%20the%20option%20of%20moving%20from%20a%20poorer%20country%20to%20a%20richer%20one%20is%20not%20just%20a%20dream%20for%20billions%20of%20people.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20entirely%20realistic%20prospect.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%20she%20drew%20criticism%20when%20she%20claimed%20that%20destitute%20people%20living%20rough%20on%20city%20pavements%20had%20made%20a%20%E2%80%9Clifestyle%20choice%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20remarks%20have%20escalated%20since%20pro-Palestine%20mass%20demonstrations%20have%20been%20held%20in%20London%20each%20Saturday%20involving%20over%20100%2C000%20people.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20evidence%20for%20anyone%20who%20watched%20the%20marches%2C%20she%20has%20said%20several%20times%20that%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Chate%20marches%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%C2%A0%C2%A0of%20last%20week%20she%20ignored%20requests%20from%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20office%20to%20tone%20down%20an%20incendiary%20article%20in%20The%20Times%20in%20which%20she%20said%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20have%20seen%20with%20our%20own%20eyes%20that%20terrorists%20have%20been%20valorised%2C%20Israel%20has%20been%20demonised%20as%20Nazis%20and%20Jews%20have%20been%20threatened%20with%20further%20massacres%E2%80%9D%20She%20also%20accused%20the%20London%20police%20of%20%E2%80%9Cplaying%20favourites%E2%80%9D%20towards%20Left-wing%20protesters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20article%2C%20Braverman%20was%20behaving%20as%20no%20Home%20Secretary%20has%20done%20in%20living%20memory%2C%20stirring%20up%20hatred%20and%20undermining%20the%20police%20instead%20of%20showing%20calm%20leadership.%20It%20was%20an%20especially%20controversial%20time%20because%20it%20coincided%20with%20the%20weekend%E2%80%99s%20annual%20Remembrance%20ceremonies%20for%20those%20fallen%20in%20two%20world%20wars%20and%20other%20battles.%20She%20wanted%20the%20marches%20cancelled%20but%20the%20London%20police%20chief%20said%20that%20was%20neither%20necessary%20not%20justified%20by%20current%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20would%20not%20hesitate%20to%20change%20the%20terror%20laws%20%E2%80%9Cif%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20need%E2%80%9D%20in%20order%20to%20combat%20%E2%80%9Cutterly%20odious%20bad%20actors%E2%80%9D%20exploiting%20gaps%20in%20the%20legislation%20to%20stir%20up%C2%A0anti-Semitism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98No-one%20better%20than%20Suella%E2%80%A6%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%20Sunak%20now%20faces%20were%20illustrated%20by%20Sir%20John%20Hayes%2C%20a%20prominent%20right-wing%20MP%20and%20a%20member%20of%20a%20group%20that%20wrote%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%C2%A0%C2%A0this%20morning%20asking%20him%20not%20to%20sack%20Braverman.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%C2%A0no%20one%20better%20than%20Suella%20Braverman%C2%A0to%20help%20Rishi%20Sunak%20deliver%20what%20he%20has%20made%20a%20defining%20(immigration)%20policy%20for%20him%20and%20the%20Government.%20I%20am%20sure%20they%20will%20collaborate%20to%20do%20so%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(UK)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20policy%2C%20her%20main%20setback%20has%20been%20that%20she%20has%20failed%20to%20solve%20the%20major%20problem%20of%20stopping%20boat%20people%20crossing%20the%20Channel%20from%20France.%20The%20supreme%20court%20will%20rule%20on%20Wednesday%20on%20the%20lawfulness%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20plan%20to%20deport%20plane-loads%20of%20these%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20Rwanda.%20Both%20Sunak%20and%20Braverman%20have%20seen%20this%20as%20a%20key%20policy.%20It%20will%20now%20become%20the%20first%20challenge%20for%20Cleverly%20%E2%80%93%20and%20an%20opportunity%20for%20Braverman%20to%20stake%20out%20her%20future%20policy%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20significance%20of%20her%20role%20as%20home%20secretary%2C%20and%20of%20her%20dismissal%2C%20goes%20far%20wider%20than%20the%20boatpeople.%20At%20a%20time%20of%20rising%20populism%20internationally%20and%20growing%20nationalism%2C%20her%20extreme%20views%20strike%20a%20chord%20among%20Conservative%20Party%20grassroots%20and%20she%20could%20replace%20Sunak%20as%20party%20leader%20if%2C%20as%20seems%20likely%2C%20he%20loses%20the%20next%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2264%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fridingtheelephant.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F11%2F14%2Fsunak-sacks-troublesome-braverman-and-reinvents-ex-pm-cameron%2F%5C%22%3Eblog%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2264%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fvrbneo%5C%22%3EJohn%20Elliott%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699937738000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14102103%2FUntitled-design.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Frishi-sunak-suella-braverman-david-cameron%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20weeks%20of%20declining%20populari