and%20Georgia%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Flive%2F2023%2F11%2F06%2Fus%2Ftrump-biden-times-siena-poll-updates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%2FSiena%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20many%20in%20the%20party%20fretted%2C%20wondering%20what%20Biden%20could%20do%20to%20counter%20the%20former%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20some%20Democrats%20have%20suggested%20that%20Biden%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-defends-2024-presidential-campaign-age-wisdom-knowledge-ruhle-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20longtime%20institution%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Washington%20who'll%20turn%2081%20years%20old%20next%20week%2C%20should%20step%20aside%20for%20a%20younger%20generation%20of%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Jim%20Messina%20%E2%80%94%20who%20in%202012%20managed%20then-President%20Barack%20Obama's%20successful%20reelection%20bid%20%E2%80%94%20has%20a%20message%20for%20Democrats%20worried%20about%20Biden's%20current%20standing%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20panic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2Fmagazine%2F2023%2F11%2F13%2Fobama-2012-campaign-manager-advice-00126736%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20Politico%20Magazine%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20Monday%2C%20Messina%2C%20who%20also%20served%20as%20a%20White%20House%20deputy%20chief%20of%20staff%20for%20operations%20under%20Obama%2C%20wrote%20that%20his%20onetime%20boss%20dealt%20with%20similar%20political%20headwinds%20in%202011%20%E2%80%94%20a%20year%20before%20the%20then-president%20was%20set%20to%20face%20voters%20again%20after%20his%20historic%202008%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20year%20before%20a%20presidential%20election%2C%20it%20is%20just%20too%20early%20to%20get%20an%20accurate%20read%20on%20how%20the%20people%20will%20actually%20vote%2C%26quot%3B%20Messina%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMessina%20argued%20that%20at%20this%20stage%20of%20the%20race%2C%20voters%20who%20are%20already%20deeply%20attuned%20to%20politics%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20are%20mostly%20reflected%20in%20early%20polling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20either%20die-hard%20partisans%20or%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20swing%20voters%20aren't%20tuned%20in%20yet%20and%20may%20not%20decide%20who%20to%20back%20until%20very%20late%2C%20and%20they%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20will%20decide%20this%20election.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20Obama%20faced%20a%20new%20GOP%20House%20majority%2C%20a%20Democratic%20Senate%20majority%20that%20had%20been%20sharply%20reduced%20in%20the%20previous%20year's%20midterm%20elections%2C%20and%20an%20economy%20that%20was%20slowly%20recovering%20from%20the%20Great%20Recession.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-really-behind-the-tea-party-movement-2011-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Tea%20Party%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20in%20full%20force%2C%20with%20many%20observers%20assuming%20they'd%20carry%20over%20their%20energy%20into%20the%20fast-approaching%20presidential%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Obama%20went%20on%20to%20defeat%20Republican%20Mitt%20Romney%20in%202012%2C%20capturing%20virtually%20every%20major%20swing%20state%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMessina%20argued%20that%20Democrats%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20lay%20out%20a%20clear%20and%20solid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-economy-is-bidenomics-working-policies-progress-unnoticed-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20voters%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20Obama%20earned%20low%20marks%20on%20the%20economy%20from%20voters%20in%202011%20but%20significantly%20improved%20his%20standing%20on%20the%20issue%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20veteran%20political%20advisor%20also%20said%20that%20Biden%20should%20work%20to%20ensure%20t