%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-1699622733-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-1699622733-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-1699622733-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-1699622733-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-334026%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAsha%E2%80%99s%20book%20was%20translated%20into%20English%20for%20the%20first%20time%20by%20her%20granddaughter-in-law%2C%20Tanvi%20Srivastava.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2095%2C%20Asha%20%3Cem%3Esan%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20title%20equivalent%20to%20Ms%20in%20Japanese)%20lives%20in%20Patna%2C%20Bihar.%20The%20experiences%20of%20her%20unusual%20life%20which%20she%20had%20jotted%20down%20on%20scraps%20of%20papers%20and%20letters%20became%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20personal%20accounts%20of%20the%20Indian%20freedom%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompiled%20into%20a%20diary%20which%20was%20later%20published%20in%201992%2C%20the%20original%20Hindi%20book%20is%20now%20translated%20into%20English%20for%20the%20first%20time%20by%20her%20granddaughter-in-law%2C%20Tanvi%20Srivastava.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETitled%20%3Cem%3EThe%20War%20Diary%20of%20Asha-san%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20book%20is%20a%20firsthand%20account%20of%20the%20young%20girl%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20war%20in%20Japan%20while%20being%20committed%20to%20the%20independence%20cause%20of%20her%20faraway%20homeland%2C%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20learning%20Hindi%20to%20using%20machine%20guns%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201928%20in%20Kobe%2C%20Japan%2C%20to%20Indian%20freedom%20fighters%20Sati%20Sen%20and%20Anand%20Mohan%20Sahay%20%E2%80%94%20who%20met%20